EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to allowing on-site disposal of storm water runoff to improve the quality of New York city waters and enhance the potential for recreational use of the city's waterfronts.

EventItemMatterName: Standing to commence an action to foreclose a mortgage. (A.11465/S.8174)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring the department of information technology and telecommunication to publish annually a public data directory.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of information technology and telecommunication to publish annually a public data directory.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Juvenile Justice
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on New York State to reduce the notification period required before the New York State Office of Child and Family Services is permitted to close a correctional facility.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing paid family leave to private employees.
EventItemMatterName: Providing paid family leave to private employees.

EventItemMatterName: Reducing the maximum fine amount for violations of vending regulations and defining unrelated violations of vending rules and regulations as separate offenses.

EventItemMatterName: Concerning the increase in the amount to be expended in 7 BIDS.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.4255, authorizing the New York State Departments of Health and Environmental Conservation to commission a study on the effects of exposure to long-term, low radiation emissions from cellular phone antennas on human beings, specifically adolescents.
EventItemMatterName: Health and Environmental Conservation to commission a study on the effects of exposure to long-term, low radiation emissions from cellular phone antennas on human beings, specifically adolescents. (A.4255)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.4374, which would prohibit cellular towers or related equipment within five hundred feet of a school building in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibit cellular towers or related equipment within five hundred feet of a school building in NYC. (A.4374)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Lower Manhattan Redevelopment
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey to reenter into negotiations with St. Nicholas Greek Orthodox Church in an effort to have the church rebuilt after being destroyed in the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks.
EventItemMatterName: Reenter into negotiations with St. Nicholas Greek Orthodox Church in an effort to have the church rebuilt after being destroyed in the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass legislation that would create a presumption that, when testifying at trial, an undercover police officer is endangered by his or her identity being made public, and would require the court to take all necessary measures to protect the officer’s identity.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Legislature to pass legislation that would create a presumption that, when testifying at trial, an undercover police officer is endangered by his or her identity being made public, and would require the court to take all necessary measures to protect
